---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Text from "@/components/fundations/elements/Text.astro";
import Wrapper from "@/components/fundations/containers/Wrapper.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section class="bg-white overflow-hidden">
    <Wrapper variant="standard" class="py-16 lg:py-24 max-w-3xl">
      <Text tag="h1" variant="displayLG" class="tracking-tight text-base-900">
        About Ariana
      </Text>
      <div class="prose prose-base mt-8 text-base-600 max-w-none">
        <p>
          I'm Bay Area born and raised — first-gen college graduate from San
          Francisco State. I didn't have parents who walked me through corporate
          recruiting. I figured it out through hundreds of applications, campus
          leadership, and a lot of trial and error.
        </p>
        <p>
          I applied to over 100 internships from November through May. I tracked
          everything in a spreadsheet, networked on LinkedIn, and eventually
          landed at Uber. Today I'm in sales at a tech company — a path I
          didn't predict, but one that fits.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Intern to Impact</strong> is the resource I wish existed for my
          younger cousin, my Psi Chi team, and anyone at a state school who wants
          corporate or tech but doesn't know where to start.
        </p>
        <p>
          The advice here isn't universal law — it's what worked for me. Take
          what helps, skip what doesn't, and build your own reps.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Wrapper>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
